            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-12 14:19:02" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a sharp projection of a woody plant (though possibly a splinter of wood) with the implication of its causing injury and discomfort</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>thorn</Gloss>
                <Gloss>splinter</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In the NT σκόλοψ occurs only in the figurative expression σκόλοψ τῇ σαρκί ‘thorn in the flesh,’ and this expression has been subject to a number of different interpretations (see {D:22.20}).</Comments>
